  "doc_id": "834",
  "text": "Allan and Charles (ibid.) draw upon Althusseur's concept of interpellation, especially as evoked by [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] . Although the authors do not fully explain what these interpellations are, from [CITATION_3] we understand this to be a process of bringing a subject into being in a social sense through language, as people are 'hailed' (called and named) and respond or take on that name. These interpellations: ''hail[s]' and construct[s] the normative, middle class girl subject …. At the same time, silently infer[ing] the failed 'other' who is required for the production of the norm' (Allan and Charles, 2014.342) . Few studies have examined the intersection between gender and race/ethnicity, and this paper addresses this gap.",
